text: It looks like the task title is being shown twice in the Execute details sidebar - at the top, and again next to the status. Please remove the smaller title, and only show the title at the top of the sidebar.

proposedTasks.title: Remove duplicate task title from Execute detail sidebar
proposedTasks.description:
In the Execute phase task detail sidebar, the task title currently appears twice: once as the sidebar heading and again inline next to the status badge. Remove the smaller inline title next to the status so the title only appears once at the top of the sidebar.

Acceptance criteria:
- Task title renders exactly once in the detail sidebar, as the top-level heading
- The status badge remains visible but is no longer accompanied by a redundant title
- No layout shift or visual regression in the sidebar when a task is selected
- Verify across light and dark themes

taskTitles: Remove duplicate task title from Execute detail sidebar
